title: Pres. Ramaphosa in Rwanda for the launch of African Continental Free Trade Area
description:
President Cyril Ramaphosa is in the Rwandan capital, Kigali ahead of the launch of the African Continental Free Trade Area on Wednesday.
The trade agreement will create a market of one billion people with a combined Gross Domestic Product of two and a half trillion US Dollars. South Africa is backing the deal, saying it will ease the movement of people, goods and people across the continent.

For more news, visit: sabcnews.com
